  "prompt": "Which friends do you think are the best - school friends or college friends?",
  "response": "The choice between school friends and college friends being \"better\" can be quite subjective and varies greatly from person to person. Here are some perspectives:\n\n**School Friends:**\n1. **Shared History**: These friends often share a longer history with you, as many school friendships span several years, sometimes even from childhood.\n2. **Understanding of Personal Growth**: They might have seen and understood your developmental years, watched you grow, and may have a deeper understanding of your background.\n3. **Nostalgic Bond**: School memories can be very precious, and revisiting them with old friends can be particularly nostalgic and emotionally satisfying.\n\n**College Friends:**\n1. **Shared Interests**: College friends often share more specific interests related to your academic and career paths, making conversations and activities more aligned with your current goals and aspirations.\n2. **Support During Transition**: College is a major transitional stage in life. Friends made during this time can provide critical support as you navigate independence, self-discovery, and adulthood.\n3. **Professional Network**: College friends can become valuable professional contacts later in life, aiding in career development and opportunities.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" friends depend on individual experiences, personalities, and the depth of connections formed. Some people find lifetime friendships in school, while others form more lasting bonds in college. Both sets of friends can offer unique and important contributions to your life.",
